            {
              "id": "CVE-2024-5535-openssl-fips-provider",
              "name": "RpmMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2024-5535 low vulnerability for openssl-fips-provider package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A flaw was found in OpenSSL. Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Information Exposure through the SSL_select_next_proto function. This flaw allows an attacker to cause unexpected application behavior or a crash by exploiting the buffer overread condition when the function is called with a zero-length client list. This issue is only exploitable if the application is misconfigured to use a zero-length server list and mishandles the 'no overlap' response in ALPN or uses the output as the opportunistic protocol in NPN."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-5535",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2024-5535\nSeverity: low\nPackage: openssl-fips-provider\nVersion: 1:3.5.5-2.el10_2\nFix Version: \nType: rpm\nLocation: /usr/lib/sysimage/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite\nData Namespace: redhat:distro:redhat:10\nLink: [CVE-2024-5535](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-5535)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2024-5535**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| low  | openssl-fips-provider  | 1:3.5.5-2.el10_2  |   | rpm  | /usr/lib/sysimage/rpm/rpmdb.sqlite  | redhat:distro:redhat:10  | [CVE-2024-5535](https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-5535)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:rpm/rocky/openssl-fips-provider@3.5.5-2.el10_2?arch=x86_64\u0026distro=rocky-10.2\u0026epoch=1\u0026upstream=openssl-3.5.5-2.el10_2.src.rpm"
                ],
                "security-severity": "5.9"
              }
            },
